lenders.name: Eco-Benin
lenders.loan_because: I want to win additionnal revenue to community-based tours by raising rabbits being sold to village restaurants for tourists foods
lenders.occupational_info:
A community-based ecotourism initiative is being developed by Benin Ecotourism Concern (Eco-Benin NGO) with the riparian communities of Aheme Lake in the southern area of Benin. The initiative is being conducting upon an agreement between Eco-Benin and the local communities. There tourists enjoy the charm of the Ahémé Lake and the beauty of its beaches. The site is composed of an ecotourism camp built upon village houses models and there is also two camping area on the beaches of the lake. All the tourism activities are managed the villagers with benefit using for local projects. An ecotourism association is established by representative from the 4 villages surrounding the Lake. Seven local tours have been set up by villagers including the village culture and natural attractions (bird, water, monkeys, mangroves, thermal springs, and belvedere). Tours integrated biking, canoeing, trekking, initiation in local cooking and handcraft while visitors share knowledge with riparian communities. The riverside voodoo traditions and existing fishing techniques are taken into account. Eco-volunteering is also well developed in the riparian villages. 
To win additional revenues, the villagers are promoting small activities such as rabbit raising and goats raising. But since the interest for these activities is now growing, they need resources to overcome the challenge. So, we create the rabbit bank. This initiative permits anybody to lend us money to buy rabbits that we give to beneficiaries who give back the loan when they start selling animals.
